; Regression test for issue #1689: Error: Timelog check-out date less than
; corresponding check-in.
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1689
;
; When a timelog has an open check-in whose timestamp is in the future
; relative to the effective "now", ledger used to auto-close that entry
; at CURRENT_TIME() and then fail with "Timelog check-out date less than
; corresponding check-in".  Such future check-ins represent work that
; has not yet started, so close() should silently drop them -- reports
; still compute cleanly and the entry is picked up once "now" passes
; the check-in time.

i 2018-11-10 08:16:00 PROJ1
o 2018-11-10 08:18:00
i 2018-11-10 08:18:00 PROJ2

; Before the PROJ2 check-in is reached, only PROJ1 is reported and
; there is no error.
test --now 2018/11/10 register --time-colon -p 2018/11/10
18-Nov-10                       PROJ1                          2:0m         2:0m
end test

; Once "now" advances past the PROJ2 check-in, PROJ2 is auto-closed at
; "now" and shows elapsed time as usual.
test --now 2018/11/11 register --time-colon -p 2018/11/10
18-Nov-10                       PROJ1                          2:0m         2:0m
18-Nov-10                       PROJ2                        15:42h       15:44h
end test
